\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {(a) Phase~1} experimental matrix. Cell shade encodes relative IID convergence (green~=~high, blue~=~medium, red~=~low); KD methods are competitive with weight-sharing on CSI datasets while requiring no weight exchange. \textbf  {(b) Phase~2} heterogeneity ablation. \emph  {Top}: tier composition per configuration. \emph  {Bottom}: qualitative accuracy trend — KD methods are robust to tier diversity (soft-label aggregation is architecture-agnostic); FedAvg degrades as tier imbalance grows.}}{4}{}\protected@file@percent }
